      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since your medical evaluation was clear, the focus shifts to environmental factors, and specialized frequencies can indeed be very difficult to detect with standard consumer sound meters. These lower, infrasonic frequencies are often below the range where typical audio recording equipment is designed to capture effectively. Consider looking into specialized environmental monitoring equipment or consulting with an acoustical engineer who has expertise in detecting very low-frequency vibrations in a home setting. Documenting the exact times and locations is crucial, as this pattern-based evidence is vital for any investigation.",
      "source": "target",
